4.5 Global Stability and Robustness to Noise

Theorem 11 (Global Stability in Decay‑Dominated Regime). If the decay rates satisfy \mu_k > r_k + \sigma \sum_j \tilde{S}_{jk} for all k, then the origin \mathbf{x}=0 is globally asymptotically stable. Moreover, there exists a linear Lyapunov function V(X) = \sum_{i,k} x_i^k such that \dot{V} \le -\gamma V for some \gamma>0, implying exponential convergence.

Proof. Direct computation:

\dot{V} = \sum_{i,k} \dot{x}_i^k.

Using the bounds x_i^k(1 - x_i^k/K_k) \le x_i^k and x_i^j(1-x_i^k) \le x_i^j, we obtain

\dot{V} \le \sum_{i,k} \left( r_k x_i^k + \sigma\sum_{j\neq k}\tilde{S}_{jk} x_i^j - \mu_k x_i^k \right) \le \sum_{i,k} \left( r_k + \sigma\sum_j \tilde{S}_{jk} - \mu_k \right) x_i^k.

The condition ensures the coefficient is negative, so \dot{V} \le -\gamma V with \gamma = \min_k (\mu_k - r_k - \sigma\sum_j \tilde{S}_{jk}) > 0. ∎

